.\" Man page for wxmine — wxWidgets Minesweeper
.\" Translated from wxmine.chm (Minesweeper Help).
.TH WXMINE 6 "2026-04-19" "wxmine" "Games Manual"
.SH NAME
wxmine \- a wxWidgets port of the classic Minesweeper game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wxmine
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Minesweeper
is a challenging game of strategy and luck.
.PP
When playing Minesweeper you are presented with a mine field, and your
objective is to locate all the mines as quickly as possible.
To do this, you uncover the squares on the game board that do not contain
mines, and you mark the squares that do contain mines.
The trick is determining which squares are which.
.PP
If you uncover all the squares without mines, you win; if you uncover a mine
instead of marking it, you lose the game.
The faster you play, the lower your score.
You can use the counters at the top of the playing area to keep track of your
progress.
.PP
The counter in the upper-right corner of the playing area is a timer, which
displays your playing time in seconds.
The timer does not begin counting until you select a square.
.PP
The counter in the upper-left corner of the playing area initially indicates
the number of mines hidden in the mine field.
Every time you mark a square as a mine, this number decreases by one, even if
you incorrectly mark a square.
.SH PLAYING THE GAME
The object of Minesweeper is to correctly mark all mines as quickly as
possible without uncovering one.
.SS Choosing a skill level
From the
.B Game
menu, choose
.BR Beginner ", " Intermediate ", or " Expert .
The higher the skill level, the larger the mine field.
.TP
.B Beginner
9 \(mu 9 board, 10 mines.
.TP
.B Intermediate
16 \(mu 16 board, 40 mines.
.TP
.B Expert
30 \(mu 16 board, 99 mines.
.TP
.B Custom
9\(en30 wide, 9\(en24 tall, 10\(en999 mines (capped at (W\-1)\(mu(H\-1)).
.SS Starting a new game
From the
.B Game
menu, choose
.BR New ,
or press
.BR F2 .
You can also click the yellow \(lqhappy face\(rq at the top of the game board.
.SS Locating the mines
.IP 1. 4
To uncover a square, select it using the left mouse button.
If the square is a mine, you lose.
.IP 2. 4
If the square isn't a mine, a number appears.
This number represents the number of mines in the surrounding eight squares.
.IP 3. 4
To mark a square as a mine, select it with the right mouse button.
To mark a square you are uncertain about, point to it and click twice with
the right mouse button.
This marks the square with a question mark
.RB ( ? ).
Later, you can either mark the square as a mine, or uncover it.
.SH RULES OF THE GAME
.IP \(bu 2
The playing area is a mine field, simulated by a grid of squares.
Initially, all the squares are covered.
.IP \(bu 2
To uncover a square, point to it and click the left mouse button.
You continue to uncover squares until only the squares containing mines are
covered.
.IP \(bu 2
If you uncover a square that does not contain a mine, it either contains a
number or is blank.
If the square contains a number
.IR N ,
then there are
.I N
mines in the surrounding eight squares.
If the square is blank, there are no mines in the surrounding eight squares.
.IP \(bu 2
If you uncover a blank square, the surrounding eight squares are uncovered
automatically because there cannot be any mines under them.
.IP \(bu 2
If you know that a square is a mine, you can mark the square.
.IP \(bu 2
If you uncover a square that contains a mine, the game is over and all the
mines are displayed.
.PP
You can also \(lqclear around\(rq an uncovered number square whose mine has
already been marked.
For example, two squares labeled 1 may both be touching a marked square.
If you clear around the uncovered squares, you may uncover additional squares
that do not contain mines.
If you clear around a square whose mine is already marked, the surrounding
numbered squares are uncovered.
.SS Clearing around a square
Point to the numbered square, and then click both mouse buttons at the same
time (or the middle mouse button).
If there are other squares whose mines have been marked, they will be
uncovered for you.
.PP
You are not allowed to clear around a square if you have not marked enough
mines in the surrounding eight squares, or if the square is covered.
For example, if you try to clear around a square labeled 3, and you have
marked only two squares with mines, nothing will happen.
Likewise, nothing happens if you try to clear around an uncovered square.
.PP
If you clear around a square, and there is an unmarked mine in the
surrounding eight squares, it is uncovered and the game is over.
If you clear around a square whose mines are incorrectly marked and a mine is
uncovered, the game is over.
.SH KEEPING SCORE
Minesweeper scoring is simple.
The counter in the upper-right corner of the playing area indicates your
playing time.
The faster you find all the mines, the better your score.
.PP
To see a list of your fastest playing times, choose
.B Best Times
from the
.B Game
menu.
.SH MARKING A SQUARE
Knowing when to mark a square as a mine is the key to winning the game.
.TP
.B To uncover a square
Point to the square, and click the left mouse button.
.TP
.B To mark a square as a mine
Point to the square, and click the right mouse button once.
.TP
.B To mark a square as a question mark
Point to the square, and click the right mouse button twice.
.TP
.B To change a square marked as a mine into a question mark
Point to the square, and click the right mouse button once.
.TP
.B To clear a square marked as a mine
Point to the square, and click the right mouse button twice.
.PP
Once you have marked at least one square as a mine, you may be able to safely
uncover more squares by \(lqclearing around\(rq them.
.SH STRATEGIES AND HINTS
.IP \(bu 2
If an uncovered square is labeled 1, and there is only one covered square
touching it, that covered square must be a mine.
.IP \(bu 2
If an uncovered square already has the correct number of adjacent mines
marked, clear around it.
.IP \(bu 2
Don't guess.
If you can't figure out how to move, try approaching the area from a
different direction or marking squares with question marks.
.SH MENU OPTIONS
.TP
.B Game \(-> Marks (?)
Toggles the third right-click state (\(lq?\(rq) on or off.
.TP
.B Game \(-> Color
Toggles between the colour and black-and-white sprite sheets.
.TP
.B Game \(-> Sound
Toggles the tick / win / lose sound effects.
.TP
.B Game \(-> Best Times\&...
Shows the persistent high-score table.
.SH KEYBOARD
.TP
.B F1
Help.
.TP
.B F2
Start a new game.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.wxmine
Configuration and high-score data on Linux
.RB ( wxConfig
backing store).
.SH NOTES
The first cell you reveal is always safe \(em if you happen to click on a
mine, it is relocated to the first available empty cell.
